    "note": "Phase A.1 routing-mechanism fixture. The HyperLiquid UsdSend -> erc20_transfer mapping is a B.3 placeholder: HyperLiquid signs an L1 action (HyperliquidTransaction:UsdSend) whose `amount` is a DECIMAL STRING (e.g. '100.0') that cannot parse as a U256, and whose value moves USDC on the HyperLiquid L1 (no EVM token-transfer calldata). We map `recipient` from the message `destination` and pin `amount` to a literal 0 + a zero token address purely so the payload ROUTES to a valid Erc20TransferAction body and exercises the by-typed-data index + WASM typed-data routing. Real HyperLiquid action semantics (decimal amount parse, USDC L1 identity, signatureChainId binding) are a B.3 concern. selector/verifying_contract are 0x000..00 placeholders (HyperLiquid uses chain-id-scoped domains, not a real verifying contract).",
